@startuml
!theme cerulean
title UC-09 - Activity Diagram: Manage Dead Letter Queue (DLQ)

start

:1. System Operator accesses DLQ Management Module;

:2. System displays list of failed messages (with error reason, timestamp, profile);

if (Action?) then (Search)
  :3. Enter search criteria (Profile, Error Type, Date Range...);
  :4. System returns filtered results;

elseif (Action?) then (View Detail)
  :3. Select a message;
  :4. System shows full payload and error details;

elseif (Action?) then (Reprocess)
  :3. Select message(s);
  :4. System performs validation & dependency check;
  if (Can Reprocess?) then (Yes)
    :5. Send message back to Mapping Engine;
    :6. Update status = Reprocessing;
  else (No)
    :Show warning;
    detach
  endif

elseif (Action?) then (Archive / Delete)
  :3. Select message(s);
  :4. Confirm action;
  :5. System archives message (Soft Delete) and records reason;
endif

:7. System logs full audit trail (who, what, when, before/after);

stop

@enduml